_olex2_refinement_description     
;
1. Fixed Uiso
 At 1.2 times of:
  All C(H) groups, All N(H,H,H) groups
2. Restrained distances
 F4A-B1A \\sim F1-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F3A-B1A \\sim F4-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F1A-B1A \\sim F2-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F2A-B1A \\sim F3-B1
 with sigma of 0.02
 F4A-F3A \\sim F1-F4
 with sigma of 0.04
 F4A-F1A \\sim F1-F2
 with sigma of 0.04
 F4A-F2A \\sim F1-F3
 with sigma of 0.04
 F3A-F1A \\sim F4-F2
 with sigma of 0.04
 F3A-F2A \\sim F4-F3
 with sigma of 0.04
 F1A-F2A \\sim F2-F3
 with sigma of 0.04
3. Uiso/Uaniso restraints and constraints
All non-hydrogen atoms have similar U: within 2A with sigma of 0.04 and sigma
for terminal atoms of 0.08 within 2A
4. Rigid body (RIGU) restrains
 All non-hydrogen atoms
 with sigma for 1-2 distances of 0.004 and sigma for 1-3 distances of 0.004
5. Others
 Sof(F4)=Sof(F1)=Sof(F2)=Sof(F3)=Sof(B1)=1-FVAR(1)
 Sof(F4A)=Sof(F3A)=Sof(F2A)=Sof(F1A)=Sof(B1A)=FVAR(1)
6.a Aromatic/amide H refined with riding coordinates:
 C2(H2), C3(H3), C4(H4), C6(H6), C5(H5)
6.b Idealised Me refined as rotating group:
 N1(H1A,H1B,H1C)
;

